<img class="aligncenter wp-image-1412677" src="https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/4CDB4C9E-1F65-4304-82AD-85F4DDEC2917.jpeg?resize=500%2C375&#038;ssl=1" alt="" width="500" height="375" srcset="https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/4CDB4C9E-1F65-4304-82AD-85F4DDEC2917.jpeg?w=300&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/4CDB4C9E-1F65-4304-82AD-85F4DDEC2917.jpeg?resize=58%2C44&amp;ssl=1 58w, https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/4CDB4C9E-1F65-4304-82AD-85F4DDEC2917.jpeg?resize=260%2C194&amp;ssl=1 260w, https://i2.wp.com/www.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2020/06/4CDB4C9E-1F65-4304-82AD-85F4DDEC2917.jpeg?resize=173%2C130&amp;ssl=1 173w" sizes="(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" data-recalc-dims="1" /> The Edo governorship primary election of All Progressives Congress (APC) on Monday held across the 18 local government areas of the state peacefully. Correspondents who monitored the exercise reported that the exercise witnessed large turnout amidst peaceful process in the centres visited. The three aspirants who stood for the election were former deputy governor, Dr Pius Odubu; Pastor Osagie Ize-Iyamu, and Mr Osazee Obaze. The exercise commenced as early as 8 a.m with accreditation of card carrying party members. The Gov. Hope Uzodima-led primaries election committee ensured that APC’s card carrying members maintained the prescribed physical distancing of maximum 15 members, wearing face masks across the 192 wards of the 18 LGAs. Some of the wards monitored were ward 3 in Egor LGA, Auchi ward 1 to 4 in Etsako West LGA, ward 7 in Etsako East LGA, Ohuan, Uhi and Isi North in Uhunmwonde LGA, Ward 3 in Egor LGA and Ward 9 in Oredo LGA. There was also the presence of INEC personnel monitoring the process with security personnel who stood guard from a distance. Collation of results is ongoing. NAN Vanguard News Nigeria Edo: APC, PDP, ACP and ACPN agents have so far expressed satisfaction at the on-going governorship elections in Edo state. The governorship election in Edo has recorded an impressive turnout with voters arriving at polling stations in large numbers across the state. September 28, 2016 In "News" Edo Election: The governorship election in Edo has recorded an impressive turnout with voters arriving at polling stations in large numbers across the state. September 28, 2016 In "Edo election 2016" The strong man of Edo Chief Anthony Anenih cast his vote at about 1.12 pm at Uzenema Primary School, Uromi and described turnout as impressive. He said he would not make any comments until later. July 14, 2012 In "News"